high_descs: Turn around and face the counter with the tomato on it.
Pick up the small knife with the yellow handle, closest to the tomato.
Slice the tomato with a knife.
Step forward one step, turn right for one step and turn left to face the microwave.
Open the microwave door, put the knife in the oven with the blade facing right, close the door.
Turn to the left for one step and turn right to face the tomato.
Pull out a slice from the middle of the tomato.
Turn right for one step, turn right for two steps, and turn right again to face the sink.
Put the tomato slice on the drain in the sink, on the left side. Leaving the faucet on the other side, turn on the water and rinse the tomato and take it out of the sink.
Turn right for two steps then turn left.
Put the tomato on the strip of counter between the right sink and the edge of the counter, over to the right side of the sink.
anns.task_desc: Put a rinsed tomato slice on the counter in front of the right sink.

high_descs: Turn around, go to the counter where the tomato is.
Pick up the yellow handled knife that is closest to the tomato.
Cut the tomato on the counter into slices.
Turn to the right, go to the microwave that is on the left.
Put the knife inside the microwave.
Turn to the left, go to the counter where the tomato is.
Pick up a slice of tomato that is on the counter.
Turn around, go forward, hang a right and go to the sink.
Put the tomato in the sink, rinse it off, then pick it back up.
Turn to the right, go forward, turn to the left to face the counter.
Put the tomato on the counter in front of the rightmost sink.
anns.task_desc: Put clean tomato on a counter.

high_descs: Turn around and face the dish washer.
Pick up the knife beside the tomato on top of the counter.
Slice the tomato on the counter.
Move to the microwave on the counter to your right.
Put the knife inside the microwave.
Move to the sliced tomato on the counter to your left.
Pick up a slice of the tomato,
Turn around and move to the sink on your right.
Wash the slice of tomato and pick it back up.
Move to the right sink.
Set the slice of tomato onto the sink counter.
